						<summary>

						<p>Another pillar in the hall of the temple Śrī Veṅkatēśvara (also called Sātāni maṭha).</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1334, Nandana, Chaitra śu. 5, Monday</hi> is corresponding to 1413 A.D., March 6 f.d.t. 23.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of land to the god Mulasthāna Mallaya by Liṅganna seṭṭi for the merit of his parents and maternal uncle.</p>						

						</summary>
